Reference-contexts: A Phylan board and an Ethernet board can be integrated in a node of the EMPS hardware. Software can be downloaded from the Sun host via a PC and Phylan to the EMPS hardware as described in <ref> [Jan94] </ref>. 1.2 Word conversion over Phylan A PC, needed to link Ethernet and Phylan, requires a conversion of the data format. The kernel software is downloaded from a Sun host via a PC with an Intel processor to the MC68030 processor. The kernel software initializes and controls the Phylan board. <p> It should be noticed that the times measured could be improved with a small value by recovering the changes that had to be made for the compiler bug as described in <ref> [Jan94] </ref>. With these results the timing behaviour can be used for clock synchronisation.
